<subSubSection pageId="66" pageNumber="67" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,613,710]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,613,638]" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Medium sized species; media anterior of tegmen fused in basal area with radius; ovipositor usually upcurved with tip slightly widened. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ingrisch" authorityYear="2018" box="[747,862,649,673]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllacrididae" genus="Gryllacris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="66" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[747,862,649,673]" italics="true" pageId="66" pageNumber="67">Gryllacris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the male ninth abdominal tergite not strongly modified but of normal shape and with rather short projections of various shape.
</paragraph>
